com.ibm.team.scm.client

Interface IHistoricBaselineIterator


  • public interface IHistoricBaselineIterator
    This interface can be used by the client to iterate over a a result set of baselines, which may be too large to return in a single round trip.
    Since:
    0.6

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<? extends IBaselineHandle> getBaselines()
      Returns a possibly empty list of baselines in this page.
      IHistoricBaselineIterator getPrevious(int max, org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
      Fetches baselines previous to this page.
      boolean hasPrevious()
      Returns true if getPrevious() may be called to retrieve more historic baselines and false otherwise.

    • Method Detail

      • getBaselines

        boolean hasPrevious()

      • getPrevious

        IHistoricBaselineIterator getPrevious(int max,
                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                      throws TeamRepositoryException
        Fetches baselines previous to this page. You must use the instance returned from this method to look at the new list. The receiver will continue to hold the current page.
        Parameters:
        max - The maximum number of results to return. The server may return a smaller number for whatever reason.
        monitor - For reporting progress, or null if progress reporting is not desired.
        Throws:
        TeamRepositoryException
